FBIS4-64132 "drsov103_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 National Affairs Kravchuk To Propose Solution to `Crimean Problems' 31 May Kravchuk To Propose Solution to `Crimean Problems' 31 May LD2605212694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2043 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605212694 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By UKRINFORM correspondent Viktor Kovalenko -- TASS] [Text] Kiev May 27 TASS -- Ukrainian parliament Chairman Aleksandr Moroz told a parliament session on Thursday that President Leonid Kravchuk intended to address lawmakers next Tuesday [31 May] in order to propose his solution of the Crimean problems. With this in view, the session decided to hold a closed-door plenary meeting on Tuesday morning. The speaker also announced the Ukrainian president's intention to present for parliament's consideration his nominees for the post of prime minister. Exercising his right to legislative initiatives, Kravchuk also plans to propose some amendments to the election law, Moroz said.
